external_knowledge:
AQI (Air Quality Index) is a measure of how air pollution affects the health of humans, animals, and the environment; The AQI range is typically categorized into different levels of health concern, from good to hazardous; 
Latitude and longitude are geographical coordinates used to determine a station's location on the Earth's surface; 
Air quality monitoring stations are places where the air quality is measured and recorded regularly; 
The health implications associated with different AQI ranges are guidelines for the public to understand the potential health risks of air pollution.

sql:
SELECT aqi
FROM air_quality_data
WHERE station_id = 1 AND so2 > 30;
